SUMMARY:Experience Argentina from North to South
DESCRIPTION:Experience Argentine culture through sight\, sound\, taste\, and movement in this interactive\, community-centered event. Designed as a participatory journey\, the program invites you to connect with traditions\, share stories\, and build meaningful connections across cultures. \nPart 1: Journey Through Argentina in Davis | 60 minutes \nBegin in the I-House’s lounge with an interactive exhibition highlighting five regions of Argentina. Through traditional crafts\, instruments\, textiles\, and photo displays\, you’ll explore the country’s cultural diversity while enjoying small tastings like Malbec\, dulce de leche\, and chimichurri. Argentine community members will share stories and guide the experience. \nPart 2: Folklore Dance Workshop | 90 minutes \nIn the I-House’s Community Room\, join a 90-minute dance workshop led by Veronica Flores. Through movement and music\, you’ll learn the basics of traditional dances such as carnavalito and gato in a welcoming\, beginner-friendly environment. \nPart 3: Peña-Inspired Musical Gathering | 90 minutes \nThe evening concludes outdoors with a relaxed\, live music gathering inspired by a traditional Argentine peña. Set in a social\, communal atmosphere\, this experience blends music\, conversation\, and shared space\, inviting you to listen\, dance\, and connect with others.
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/experience-argentina-from-north-to-south/
LOCATION:International House Davis\, 10 College Park\, Davis\, CA\, 95616\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/WT-2026-Becoming-Belonging-Being-and-Beyond-3.8.26.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="International House Davis":MAILTO:shahzana@ihousedavis.org
END:VEVENT
